-- Zimbabwe Won't Strictly Implement Black Ownership Law, Newsday Reports
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2010-12-07T08:42:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-07/zimbabwe-won-t-strictly-implement-black-ownership-law-newsday-reports.html
Zimbabwe won’t strictly implement a
law to compel foreign companies to sell 51 percent of their
assets to black Zimbabweans because the economy is struggling
and there is a need to attract foreign investment, Newsday
reported, citing Welshman Ncube, the country’s industry
minister.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
